    • Field Detail

      • status

        public EnumSet<FixityResult.FixityState> status
        This is a little weird here, and is vestigal from when this was a JAX-B model as well. The "state" of the fixity object is one of: - SUCCESS: the fixity check was declared successful - BAD_CHECKSUM and/or BAD_SIZE: either the checksum or the size of the bitstream didn't match the stored size - REPAIRED and BAD_*: the checksum or size failed to match, but it was automatically recovered from a different copy
